esence (absence) of NEM fields in case of\nweak lensing. Angular separation $s$ between the innermost and outermost\nrelativistic images increases (decreases) by increasing $0<|q|<1$ in absence\n(presence) of NEM fields. Corresponding magnification $r$ decreases (increases)\nby raising $0<|q|<1$ in absence (presence) of NEM fields. $s (r)$ raises\n(decreases) by increasing $|q|>>1.$\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 17 Jan 2016 22:08:13 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 30 May 2016 20:45:02 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 17 Nov 2016 18:49:59 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 2 Jan 2017 16:01:17 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Wed, 19 Apr 2017 13:17:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-03-14"}
